Vascular complications after orthotopic liver transplantation in Estonia. The aim of this study was to analyse vascular complications (VC) accompanying the introduction in Estonia of orthotopic liver transplantation (OLT) for treatment of end-stage liver disease. We present the incidence and treatment of VC occurring among our first 23 OLT in 22 patients. The 11 female and 11 male patients were aged 12 to 67 years. Their diagnoses were cholestatic disease (n = 8) hepatitis C virus (HCV) cirrhosis (n = 6)